Text.SourceString: Good day, stranger!//Oh, you just moved to the farm? Welcome to the community.//<portrait=normal>My name is <NPCName>Anne</>.
A quick word of advice from your new neighbor.//Be patient! Since last year, those darn crops aren’t growing like they used to.
They’re talking about building a community garden someday. You must have heard, right?//We offered the space behind our house, but I don’t think anybody much likes the idea.
It’s too far from the town and whatnot. Oh well!
They’re talking about building a community garden someday. You must have heard, right?//We offered the space behind our house, but I don’t think anybody much likes the idea.
It’s too far from the town and whatnot. Oh well!
I need to drop off my recycling before going to the supermarket tomorrow.
I wonder where we’ll put our recycling once the dumpster is full…
I wonder where we’ll put our recycling once the dumpster is full…
Not everybody has one of those fancy compact recycling machines.//<portrait=concerned>Ah, you know, the little machine that you put in your yard? Don’t you have one?
Oh well. No point complaining about it.
If you grow soybeans, you can use them to make tempeh.//I’m sure you already know that.
You do need a press to make tempeh, though.
I’m trying to find time to edit all this video footage before the deadline.
Wild animals might have already made a home at your farm. But they may be too shy to come out where you can see them.
There could be bees or Luwak at your farm. If you build a bee house, it might encourage them to come out…//Make them feel comfortable, that’s the trick.
Having a busy Thursday, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Yeah, us too.//<portrait=happy>Oh, you know, the usual. Wildlife… blah, blah, blah.
Having a busy Friday, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Yeah, us too.//<portrait=happy>Oh, you know, the usual. Wildlife… blah, blah, blah.
I don’t know how safe it is to live in the forest, especially with small children.
The Woodlands is as close as I’ll let <NpcName>Zoe</> get.
I think I’ll make some gnocchi and hummus for dinner.//Make a little extra for tomorrow too.
Oh no, I don’t think I have any tomatoes…//<portrait=concerned>Oh well! Hummus it is.
It’s great that <NpcName>Paul</> and I can observe wildlife around the clock, since we’re surrounded by nature.//But I also like that the woodland is so close to the school.
As a mom, I worry all the time. I don’t like <NpcName>Zoe</> walking too far, especially on rainy days.
If you look closely in the trees, you may notice some birds’ nests around the island.//<portrait=normal><NpcName>Zoe</> gets really excited when she spots one.
Oh, so you’ve done all your farming chores for the day?
Let me get this straight – you quit your job and moved to Coral Island to become a farmer?
That sounds so exciting!//<NpcName>Paul</> and I should make a documentary about you one day. It would be different from what we usually do, but it sure would be inspiring.
We want to get those little video cameras that you attach to your hat. That way, we can capture more footage.
But it’s a bit outside our budget right now… Oh well! It’s not the end of the world.
It takes us days and sometimes weeks to capture the best wildlife footage.
In this job, I believe that patience is the key.
The farm is pretty close to the ocean. I don’t know if that’s a good or bad thing for nocturnal animals.
Hmm… It would be interesting to observe wildlife behavior in different settings.
There will be plenty of time for <NpcName>Zoe</> to go on adventures. For now, I think it’s safer for her to focus on school.
I can’t do my shopping on the weekend. I’d have to take <NpcName>Zoe</> with me, and she’d want to buy all the cookies.
She can be quite strong-willed. It’s easier for me to do my shopping during the week.
There will be plenty of time for <NpcName>Zoe</> to go on adventures. For now, I think it’s safer for her to focus on school.
It’s <NpcName>Paul</>’s birthday this weekend. To be honest, I haven’t gotten anything for him yet.//I hope there’s still time.
There’s still time to make jam, I suppose!//That’ll be perfect. He loves jam.
I think I saw a couple of beavers swimming at the lake on my way here. Did you see them too?
Ah, that reminds me! I need to ask <NpcName>Paul</> to bring in some extra blankets from the shed now that it’s getting colder.//I’ll just ask him tomorrow.
Phew! Good thing we found extra blankets right before all these. I really need to organize stuff better.
What a pain to dig them up. I need boxes so I can label them. That would make things easier to find next year.
Some animals only come out when it rains. Have you noticed that too?
I need to always be ready in case we need to run out and film.
Watch your boots, will ya?
I might open up the windows tonight and let the sound of rain come in.
Let’s just hope there’s not a storm tonight.
It’s so humid today. Not even the rain helps break this humidity.
It’s Summer after all. What else can you expect?
It’s so humid today.//Oh gosh!
A little rain wouldn’t hurt, I don’t think.
Some animals only come out when it rains. Have you noticed that too?
I need to always be ready in case we need to run out and film.
Keep your jacket on, <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s freezing out.
Watch your boots, will ya?
If we were living in the middle of the forest, what would we do during a snowstorm like this?
All right, it may not be a storm, but it’s so cold out, it might as well be. Some animals are in their hideouts. They need to keep warm, you know…//<portrait=normal>Just like us.
If we were living in the middle of the forest, what would we do during a snowstorm like this?
All right, it may not be a storm, but it’s so cold out, it might as well be. Some animals are in their hideouts. They need to keep warm, you know…//<portrait=normal>Just like us.
I wonder how long the snow will last. I’m not complaining, though.
I'm here to pick up some groceries for the week. Hopefully, I’ll get everything I need.
I always seem to forget something. I wonder if that’s a grocery thing.
As soon as I get home, I’ll realize I forgot to buy something.//<portrait=concerned>It’s pretty annoying, if you ask me.
Write it down? Ha! That’s an idea.//<portrait=happy>All right. Maybe…
I can’t ask <NpcName>Paul</> to get groceries. He’d just scavenge some vegetables from the lake or something and bring them home.
I mean, there’s nothing wrong with wild vegetables.//<portrait=annoyed>But they’re different.
If you need a carrot, you can’t just come home with kale…//Or a fig.//You can’t substitute just anything for anything.
So you woke up holding an egg and somehow didn’t break it in your sleep?
Okay. That’s a funny story, but I still don’t know why you’re telling me all this.
*<NpcName>Anne</> is mumbling to herself*…Milk, eggs…
I wonder if I should get a couple bottles of milk instead of just one. But I don’t want it to go bad if nobody drinks it.//That would be such a waste.
See, I knew it!//I forgot to pick up some oil. We’re running out, and I don’t know what I’ll do.//<portrait=normal>Hey! What's up?
Oh, don’t worry about the mess. It’s never neat in here!
Just try not to step on anything, will you?
We don’t have any tea, but would you like some warm hummus, maybe?
